article.headline: Williamson powers SMU to 92-67 victory over Tulsa

images.name: SMU cruises past Tulsa
images.caption: Three of SMU's starters score in double figures in a 92-67 win over Tulsa.

article.linkText: Williamson powers SMU to 92-67 victory over Tulsa
article.story:
DALLAS -- — Samuell Williamson had 17 points and SMU beat Tulsa 92-67 in the Mustangs' American Athletic Conference opener on Sunday.

Williamson added seven rebounds and six assists for the Mustangs (6-8). Zach Nutall hit four 3-pointers and scored 17. Emory Lanier had 11 points.

Sam Griffin scored 22 to lead the Golden Hurricane (4-9, 0-2). Bryant Selebangue added 21 points and nine rebounds. Anthony Pritchard finished with nine points, five assists and six steals.

SMU took the lead with 1:16 left in the first half and never looked back.

NEXT UP

SMU's next game is Thursday against Houston on the road, and Tulsa visits Tulane on Wednesday.

------
